caption: The employees here are incredibly sweet and kind, each day they make it enjoyable to grab my daily cup of coffee. The place is also very COVID-safety friendly.

(Translated by Google) One of the best chain stores in New York. A good place to have breakfast, brunch or a bite to eat. Various versions of sandwiches, salads and wraps are available throughout the day. There are vegetarian and meat options. Up to 11 you can eat breakfast dishes - e.g. oatmeal with various toppings or simple egg dishes (fritattata or boiled hard-boiled eggs with toppings). Around noon lunch dishes are available - soups (tomato cream, lentil soup or chicken soup). There are also hot sandwiches. In addition, cakes, crosants, coffee and tea are available. There is wifi. I loved this chain in London and am very glad it seems to be doing so well in NYC.
